Package: CancerSignComp
Title: Benchmarking Cancer Prognostic Gene Signatures Against Each Other and Clinical Staging
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: 
    person("Berna", "Hukkamli", , "berna.hukkamli@sinop.edu.tr", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = ""))
Description: Provides a standardized framework for evaluating and comparing cancer
    prognostic gene signatures. Computes risk scores using weighted mean, GSVA, or
    ssGSEA methods; benchmarks multiple signatures against each other via concordance
    index (C-index); and compares signatures to TNM/AJCC clinical staging using
    Net Reclassification Improvement (NRI) and Integrated Discrimination Improvement
    (IDI). Includes Kaplan-Meier, C-index bar plot, and subgroup forest plot
    visualizations, as well as CSV and Excel export utilities.
